                <head>312. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Protocol for the Further Prolongation of the International Sugar Agreement
                    was adopted in London on November 1, 1965. The United States signed the
                    Protocol, which was negotiated as an executive agreement, on December 23, and it
                    entered into force for the United States on January 1, 1966. The Protocol
                    extended the International Sugar Agreement until December 31, 1966. For text,
                    see 16 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 1961; TIAS 5933. Additional
                    documentation on the ratification of the Protocol is in Department of State,
                    Central Files, INCO–SUGAR 4.</p>
            </div>
